WEBVTT

00:05.180 --> 00:07.046
Previously on "Mr. Mercedes"...

00:07.071 --> 00:08.406
This will be my masterpiece

00:08.447 --> 00:10.935
and will make us rich,
and it will reunite us.

00:11.035 --> 00:12.675
Roseland Hills Community Center.

00:12.708 --> 00:14.356
- It's his M.O.
- Let the police handle it.

00:14.380 --> 00:16.575
He wasn't just killing
people two years ago.

00:16.635 --> 00:17.761
He was mowing down hope.

00:17.790 --> 00:19.034
I got a lot of concerned people,

00:19.128 --> 00:21.088
especially with this
Edmund Mills gala coming up.

00:21.179 --> 00:22.747
He wants me. I'm his target.

00:22.814 --> 00:24.241
Let him come, I say. Let him come.

00:24.276 --> 00:26.677
Do we have a retired detective
compromising this investigation?

00:26.860 --> 00:28.894
We do not. If anything,
that retired detective

00:28.932 --> 00:30.081
was instrumental in breaking it.

00:30.106 --> 00:31.810
This is who serviced her computer.

00:31.857 --> 00:33.691
What are you doing with the speakers?

00:33.736 --> 00:35.755
I spoke to Josh about setting
up a viewing station

00:35.780 --> 00:38.290
so kids can watch it
while their parents shop.

00:38.570 --> 00:41.098
You get the kids, you get the parents.

00:41.357 --> 00:42.803
Same as selling ice cream.

00:42.871 --> 00:45.096
We have some questions
about an Olivia Trelawney.

00:45.130 --> 00:46.630
You mean the Mercedes lady?

00:46.671 --> 00:48.369
She ever take service calls
in her home?

00:48.394 --> 00:50.395
It's always Brady Hartsfield.
She requested him.

00:50.420 --> 00:52.369
The ice-cream guy is your suspect?

00:52.394 --> 00:54.128
Been hiding in plain sight ever since.

00:54.379 --> 00:55.700
Right under my fucking nose.

00:55.725 --> 00:57.680
- Why are the police looking for me?
- How did you get in here?!

00:57.705 --> 00:59.511
Are you gonna make me ask you again?

00:59.551 --> 01:00.970
You're the Mercedes killer?

01:01.038 --> 01:03.378
Step out of the vehicle immediately!

01:06.079 --> 01:09.215
Take the house!

01:10.902 --> 01:12.187
John, you better see this.

01:12.216 --> 01:13.614
- Out!
- Everybody, out!

01:13.645 --> 01:15.174
- Go, go!
- We got to go now!

01:15.293 --> 01:16.655
Bill!

01:19.309 --> 01:21.205
It's over, partner. We got him.

01:22.786 --> 01:24.120
Maybe.

01:26.000 --> 01:32.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:55.166 --> 02:57.501
I'll take a Chipwich right after.

02:57.596 --> 02:59.322
Is that a Chipwich I hear, sir?

02:59.364 --> 03:00.764
Yeah, of course you did.

03:00.805 --> 03:02.540
- Mmm!
- Mmm!

03:02.753 --> 03:03.804
Delish!

03:03.849 --> 03:05.182
Oh, absolutely.

03:06.926 --> 03:08.360
Hi, Daddy.

03:08.459 --> 03:10.294
- Hi, Mr. Hodges.
- Hey, Bill.

03:11.916 --> 03:14.201
Hey, Mr. Hodges.

03:14.285 --> 03:15.652
The usual?

03:15.901 --> 03:17.654
Double fudge?

03:17.802 --> 03:19.804
Fatty?

03:19.829 --> 03:22.562
Bill... Bill, let me have the gun.

03:22.755 --> 03:24.242
Let me have it, come on.

03:24.362 --> 03:26.726
You go have some fun.

03:27.605 --> 03:29.874
Go on. Have some ice cream.

03:31.002 --> 03:32.135
Daddy.

03:32.203 --> 03:33.905
- Daddy!
- Go ahead.

03:33.971 --> 03:35.405
Come push me on the swing.

03:35.440 --> 03:36.474
Want a bite of mine?

03:38.743 --> 03:40.677
Don't forget your fudge!

03:50.128 --> 03:52.195
Whoo!

03:57.228 --> 04:00.888
Faster!

04:08.235 --> 04:09.915
Daddy!

04:09.994 --> 04:12.062
Allie!

04:14.281 --> 04:15.621
Daddy, help!

04:15.646 --> 04:17.398
Allie!

04:18.922 --> 04:20.483
Allie!

04:27.658 --> 04:30.360
N-o-o-o-o!

04:30.401 --> 04:31.835
Allie!

04:32.076 --> 04:34.011
Allie!

05:40.731 --> 05:42.566
It's not your day.

05:42.791 --> 05:44.194
Yeah.

05:44.219 --> 05:46.153
Had to mow all my lawns today.

05:46.337 --> 05:48.218
Speaking at this gala thing tomorrow.

05:49.674 --> 05:53.076
Man... you look like
awful fucked terrible,

05:53.217 --> 05:55.234
and you're what came out
nine months later.

05:57.367 --> 05:58.968
You all right?

06:00.344 --> 06:01.946
Yeah, haven't been sleeping good.

06:04.542 --> 06:06.210
Well, you got him.

06:11.735 --> 06:13.029
He got himself.

06:14.608 --> 06:16.842
He controlled it all,
right up to the end.

06:17.020 --> 06:18.482
No.

06:18.576 --> 06:21.311
We were closing in on him,
and he knew it.

06:21.792 --> 06:23.227
"We"?

06:24.495 --> 06:25.726
Yeah.

06:26.015 --> 06:27.417
"We."

06:38.095 --> 06:40.523
What a summer, man.

06:44.320 --> 06:45.968
Yeah, I'm gonna get back to work.

06:58.155 --> 07:00.690
Will you be needing it?

07:00.998 --> 07:02.933
No, you go ahead.

07:08.432 --> 07:11.201
You're gonna have to sit with it
sooner or later, you know.

07:14.110 --> 07:15.578
Sit with what?

07:15.714 --> 07:18.122
Your loss.

07:18.235 --> 07:19.835
Got to be on the move, Ida.

07:20.010 --> 07:22.110
Motion isn't release.

07:22.205 --> 07:23.940
It's just motion.

07:26.037 --> 07:28.093
The truth is, I need it right now.

07:32.535 --> 07:35.637
If I stop, I'll drown.

07:37.868 --> 07:40.724
When you're ready, then.

07:43.553 --> 07:45.177
My mother...

07:48.592 --> 07:50.532
...I loved her...

07:51.515 --> 07:54.550
but she tried "talking to me,"

07:54.771 --> 07:57.113
and I didn't want to be talked to.

07:57.194 --> 07:59.230
Tonight, I told her what I'd done.

07:59.355 --> 08:01.590
I thought she'd be proud,

08:01.631 --> 08:04.218
finally say I'd done something worthy.

08:04.327 --> 08:06.395
She said I was sick and repulsive,

08:06.550 --> 08:09.919
that I should be hung
by my neck for what I did.

08:10.060 --> 08:12.995
Crkkkk!

08:13.122 --> 08:14.664
So now she's gone.

08:14.770 --> 08:17.254
All gone.

08:17.388 --> 08:23.192
Just like the peas on my plate
when I was a kid

08:23.447 --> 08:25.615
All gone. I miss her.

08:25.949 --> 08:27.816
I loved her.

08:27.951 --> 08:30.621
My pretty poor mommy.

08:34.711 --> 08:38.380
And I can't live here
without her, without...

08:41.184 --> 08:45.522
I'm thinking... time to go.

08:45.983 --> 08:49.045
And guess what.

08:49.540 --> 08:53.810
I'm not sorry for hating you all,

08:54.111 --> 08:56.579
not even a little.

09:01.804 --> 09:05.841
You all walking around
in your lead boots

09:05.929 --> 09:07.298
you like to call a conscience.

09:07.323 --> 09:09.257
Well, I was born wearing none

09:09.919 --> 09:13.322
so I could soar high above you all

09:13.640 --> 09:15.996
and watch you stuff your faces

09:16.119 --> 09:18.320
and flick your remotes

09:18.502 --> 09:22.956
and pray to a god you
only half believe in.

09:23.273 --> 09:26.175
It's all just a lie.

09:26.222 --> 09:28.526
The truth is blackness.

09:28.639 --> 09:31.805
And the only thing that matters...

09:32.336 --> 09:34.637
is making a statement

09:35.037 --> 09:37.240
before you enter it.

09:40.777 --> 09:44.980
Peeling back the skin of the Earth

09:45.048 --> 09:46.727
and leaving a scar.

09:46.810 --> 09:50.045
That's what history is... scar tissue.

09:50.500 --> 09:51.910
Fuck it.

09:52.115 --> 09:53.654
I'm Audi.

09:56.720 --> 10:00.752
I painted my masterpiece
a couple years ago,

10:00.891 --> 10:05.262
and I can't imagine how I could
possibly top it.

10:08.238 --> 10:10.641
What have any of you
done to be remembered?

10:29.400 --> 10:32.635
So... good night.

10:34.248 --> 10:36.883
Good fuck.

10:37.347 --> 10:39.872
I hope you're all condemned

10:40.070 --> 10:43.218
to live your meaningless lives...

10:44.961 --> 10:48.764
over... and over

10:49.112 --> 10:51.131
for-fucking-ever.

11:03.053 --> 11:04.353
Thank you.

11:04.774 --> 11:05.933
For what?

11:05.958 --> 11:07.186
Narrowing down the location

11:07.211 --> 11:09.153
of Hartsfield's home and his job,

11:09.199 --> 11:11.267
breaking this case after we stopped.

11:11.501 --> 11:13.157
What were you two doing again?

11:14.230 --> 11:16.065
We were hung up on other cases.

11:16.112 --> 11:17.708
So that's gonna be our story?

11:17.733 --> 11:19.395
We missed catching the Mercedes killer

11:19.420 --> 11:21.087
because we were otherwise occupied?

11:21.149 --> 11:23.305
It may not play
well, but it's the truth.

11:23.860 --> 11:25.832
What if he planted other bombs behind?

11:25.929 --> 11:27.729
Brady Hartsfield wasn't the type

11:27.754 --> 11:29.265
to just slink away and kill himself,

11:29.290 --> 11:31.091
I'm telling you.

11:31.744 --> 11:33.914
We're gonna send a bomb-squad
team to clear your house,

11:33.939 --> 11:35.273
send one to Edmund Mills.

11:35.586 --> 11:37.885
Anywhere else a likely target?

11:37.974 --> 11:39.808
There's a career night tomorrow.

11:40.050 --> 11:41.170
Where?

11:41.195 --> 11:43.063
The Roseland Hotel.

11:43.199 --> 11:45.734
He went after job seekers
the first time.

11:46.122 --> 11:47.746
You're on the co-workers next?

11:47.838 --> 11:50.207
I'm on the bomb squad.
We'll sweep those areas.

11:52.103 --> 11:53.605
Bill?

11:54.751 --> 11:56.339
Your house is off-limits for a while,

11:56.364 --> 11:58.698
so why don't you stick around
in an advisory capacity.

11:58.723 --> 12:01.527
You need to sign nondisclosure
and release-of-liability forms.

12:01.552 --> 12:03.362
- You good with that?
- Grand.

12:10.660 --> 12:12.828
Miss Linklatter, thanks for coming in.

12:13.222 --> 12:14.485
How you doing?

12:15.992 --> 12:17.492
Fuckin' great.

12:18.361 --> 12:20.143
 No matter how small it may seem,

12:20.168 --> 12:22.282
if anything occurs to you
about Brady Hartsfield,

12:22.307 --> 12:23.508
you give us a call.

12:25.120 --> 12:26.428
All right.

12:28.830 --> 12:31.307
Miss "Linkletter," if you'd
come with us, please.

12:33.374 --> 12:35.075
It's "Link-later."

12:35.463 --> 12:36.721
Oh, Josh.

12:37.899 --> 12:39.671
We're having trouble
locating your store manager,

12:39.696 --> 12:41.029
Anthony Frobisher.

12:41.302 --> 12:42.603
It's his day off.

12:42.671 --> 12:44.772
We sent someone by his house.
No answer.

12:44.797 --> 12:46.564
He goes to see his dad.

12:46.828 --> 12:48.329
Yeah?

12:48.730 --> 12:50.274
Yeah, on his days off,

12:50.299 --> 12:53.334
he always goes to visit
his dad in Bedford.

12:53.433 --> 12:55.004
Let's look up a Frobisher in...

12:55.029 --> 12:58.665
The only Frobisher that comes up
in Bedford... Xavier, 69...

12:59.206 --> 13:02.476
lives on Meyers Road,
one son... Anthony.

13:04.723 --> 13:06.281
All right, right this way.

13:08.444 --> 13:10.117
Some are calling him
the Mercedes killer.

13:10.142 --> 13:11.344
I can't believe it.

13:11.997 --> 13:13.263
Wow.

13:13.307 --> 13:16.843
Police believe Brady is
a strong connection to this.

13:16.868 --> 13:19.636
Again, we're reporting live
from Elm Street...

13:19.700 --> 13:21.387
The cash wrap looks like shit,

13:21.412 --> 13:23.814
and stock from last week
is still in the back room,

13:23.892 --> 13:25.260
not on the floor.

13:27.015 --> 13:29.450
And we open in 12 minutes.

13:48.556 --> 13:50.596
Detective Dixon, please.

13:50.745 --> 13:53.567
Come on. Let's go. Let's go.

13:56.317 --> 13:58.585
We had no choice but to close, sir.

13:59.379 --> 14:00.865
Over here.

14:01.221 --> 14:04.023
Yes, I am aware of declining sales,

14:04.048 --> 14:05.535
but, sir, you are aware
that Brady Hart...

14:11.814 --> 14:14.515
I understand.
But if there's a bomb, sir...

14:24.499 --> 14:26.139
All clear.

14:27.722 --> 14:30.090
It looks like we got the all-clear.

14:30.498 --> 14:32.772
Yes, yes, right away.

14:32.999 --> 14:35.236
Abso...

14:36.145 --> 14:37.411
Where's Taylor?

14:37.484 --> 14:39.272
Dude, she fuckin' quit.

14:47.001 --> 14:50.136
These are our personal cells.

14:50.404 --> 14:53.066
24/7.

14:53.354 --> 14:54.999
We never close.

14:55.376 --> 14:57.769
You did the right thing here.

14:57.846 --> 14:59.914
You can't be too paranoid right now.

15:00.528 --> 15:01.746
Sure.

15:01.789 --> 15:03.925
No. For real.

15:08.343 --> 15:10.978
Right.

15:11.806 --> 15:13.254
Yeah, will do.

15:15.449 --> 15:16.583
Okay, yeah.

15:16.608 --> 15:17.676
Talk soon.

15:23.004 --> 15:24.873
All right, let's roll.

15:29.123 --> 15:30.857
Coroner?

15:30.985 --> 15:33.920
Brady Hartsfield had no dentist.

15:34.501 --> 15:38.071
Maybe a sole redeeming
quality was good teeth.

15:41.075 --> 15:43.477
The mother?

15:44.318 --> 15:46.788
Her dentals match, yeah,
but nothing on the son.

15:49.091 --> 15:52.127
Bomb squad's cleared this
house and Edmund Mills.

15:54.822 --> 15:56.211
The Roseland?

15:56.236 --> 15:59.472
Yeah, that was a bitch, I hear.

16:00.421 --> 16:02.070
Look, nothing went boom today,

16:02.095 --> 16:05.197
and all the likely targets
are bomb-free.

16:06.260 --> 16:07.626
That's something.

16:15.136 --> 16:16.775
Speak it.

16:17.852 --> 16:20.121
You think he's dead?

16:22.256 --> 16:23.957
Yes.

16:24.685 --> 16:26.287
I do.

16:27.048 --> 16:28.609
But?

16:28.729 --> 16:30.218
They found an egress.

16:32.941 --> 16:35.075
Hidden door in the basement.

16:35.222 --> 16:36.400
Tunnel connected.

16:38.539 --> 16:41.742
So he could've got out... anytime.

16:48.663 --> 16:51.898
