18:03.087 --> 18:04.621
What's the word?

18:04.719 --> 18:06.723
Nothing on DNA yet, but the M.E. said

18:06.788 --> 18:09.890
the female looks to have been
dead longer than the male.

18:10.104 --> 18:11.482
Well, it has to be significant

18:11.507 --> 18:13.342
if he can tell from a prelim stage.

18:13.548 --> 18:16.014
And he said he's not finding
any signs of blunt-force trauma

18:16.039 --> 18:17.506
to her corpse.

18:17.759 --> 18:20.601
He's waiting on tox work.

18:20.665 --> 18:22.768
Jesus, everybody's fuckin'
waiting on things.

18:23.057 --> 18:25.258
Isn't this the 21st century?

18:25.419 --> 18:27.103
What are you, a civilian?
This shit takes time.

18:27.156 --> 18:30.557
As I was saying, prior to tox
work, he suspects poison.

18:30.592 --> 18:33.561
Something to do with the
clench of the jaw, he said.

18:35.676 --> 18:39.370
Well... he sold it in the video
like he snapped.

18:39.453 --> 18:42.236
You don't snap and then take
the time to poison someone.

18:42.360 --> 18:44.395
Yeah. One more curio.

18:44.420 --> 18:47.145
The male <i>did</i> have blunt trauma
to the back of the head,

18:47.275 --> 18:50.084
but that's where a beam
landed in the fire,

18:50.138 --> 18:51.367
so it could be that.

18:52.848 --> 18:54.673
You coming by?

18:54.791 --> 18:56.741
I'll be in.

18:56.913 --> 18:59.851
There you go.
And, um... just in the bag?

18:59.876 --> 19:01.042
Yeah, thanks.

19:01.165 --> 19:03.367
- Thank you for shopping Supreme.
- Thank you.

19:10.901 --> 19:13.103
Hi. You've reached the
voicemail of Anthony Frobisher.

19:13.128 --> 19:14.495
Please leave a message.

19:14.520 --> 19:17.298
It's Josh... again.
You're two hours late!

19:18.543 --> 19:20.266
Hope you have a hell of a reason.

19:22.600 --> 19:24.293
Oh, thank Christ you're here.

19:24.318 --> 19:25.318
Where's Robi?

19:25.343 --> 19:27.344
I don't know. Can you watch the front?

19:27.456 --> 19:29.445
- No problem.
- I've got to run an errand.

19:44.568 --> 19:45.603
Robi!

21:01.231 --> 21:02.464
We're clear.

21:02.846 --> 21:04.120
Josh.

21:07.710 --> 21:09.420
See anything out of the ordinary?

21:13.248 --> 21:15.984
I've only been here once.

21:29.891 --> 21:32.459
No, not that I can tell.

21:33.111 --> 21:35.631
Let's sticker the door and
get a forensic crew over.

21:35.770 --> 21:37.071
Can't hurt.

21:37.138 --> 21:38.873
There was a rug here.

21:41.350 --> 21:43.200
It was here three days ago.

21:46.881 --> 21:48.950
I got one in the car.

22:57.919 --> 22:59.078
What do you got?

22:59.103 --> 23:01.438
Fuckin' crime scene is what we got.

23:01.656 --> 23:03.823
Frobisher is 6-foot, 6'1"?

23:04.917 --> 23:06.254
That sounds right.

23:06.279 --> 23:07.847
How tall is Brady?

23:07.872 --> 23:10.141
Shorter... maybe 5'8 ", 5'9".

23:15.817 --> 23:17.317
Hey, Chris, it's Pete.

23:17.365 --> 23:19.299
You in the morgue or at your desk?

23:19.777 --> 23:21.508
Great. Um...

23:21.644 --> 23:25.646
I need a height on the male
corpse from Elm Street.

23:26.040 --> 23:28.309
Yeah.

23:29.197 --> 23:30.999
Got it. Thanks.

23:33.648 --> 23:35.048
Corpse in Brady Hartsfield's bed

23:35.089 --> 23:37.425
was 6 feet, 1 1/2 inches.

23:41.810 --> 23:44.043
And noone's seen Brady Hartsfield's co-worker

23:44.068 --> 23:45.463
since the night of the explosion.

23:46.715 --> 23:47.829
I know it's crazy, but, uh...

23:47.854 --> 23:50.549
But it's not impossible, either. Fuck.

23:51.112 --> 23:52.613
I'd say he's alive.

23:52.638 --> 23:55.073
He's staying under until he can
make another statement,

23:55.098 --> 23:56.898
bigger than the last one.

23:56.923 --> 23:57.993
You think the gala?

23:58.018 --> 23:59.819
Half the town will be there.

23:59.844 --> 24:01.819
The other half will be at
career night at the Roseland.

24:01.844 --> 24:03.711
Last time, he did go after job seekers.

24:03.951 --> 24:05.785
Edmund Mills is easier to secure.

24:05.879 --> 24:08.748
The Roseland has 300 rooms, an
attached convention center,

24:08.773 --> 24:11.308
entrances off that,
the street, the garages...

24:11.686 --> 24:13.354
River ferry.

24:13.715 --> 24:15.379
If I'm him and I'm looking for a target

24:15.424 --> 24:18.626
with the highest possibility
of success, it's the Roseland.

24:18.873 --> 24:21.508
- Agreed.
- Shit, shit, shit.

24:22.426 --> 24:24.838
You two get back to the station.

24:25.027 --> 24:26.433
I want your laptop.

24:26.484 --> 24:28.637
See if there's anything our guys
can find in what he sent you,

24:28.662 --> 24:30.296
anything that might tip his hand.

24:30.365 --> 24:31.832
I'll go get it.

24:32.213 --> 24:35.586
I'll talk to the mayor, see
how he wants to proceed.

25:04.212 --> 25:06.105
Is there any tangible proof of this?

25:06.180 --> 25:09.416
No, but if he's alive,
the career night at the Roseland

25:09.441 --> 25:11.542
would make for an obvious target.

25:11.592 --> 25:13.313
The gala would be the other.

25:13.384 --> 25:15.218
People are already
lined up at the gala.

25:15.309 --> 25:17.076
 If I had one specific threat,

25:17.101 --> 25:19.470
anything to justify
canceling it, I would.

25:19.501 --> 25:21.502
You can't shut it down
on conjecture, Brooke.

25:22.466 --> 25:24.298
And what about the Roseland?

25:24.606 --> 25:26.818
Am I supposed to kick
300 guests to the curb?

25:26.968 --> 25:28.402
Who's already through the gates?

25:29.164 --> 25:30.834
Performers, vendors,

25:30.872 --> 25:32.907
some V.I.P.s,
people with special needs.

25:34.156 --> 25:36.324
I'm gonna send a detachment
to the Roseland

25:36.349 --> 25:38.677
and a small detail to the gala.

25:38.766 --> 25:40.467
We're gonna be thin in both places.

25:40.515 --> 25:42.716
I can beef up private security.

25:42.750 --> 25:45.418
Need all the help we can get.

25:45.946 --> 25:49.499
Here's a picture of Hartsfield.
Make copies, pass it out.

26:17.001 --> 26:18.074
Hello?

26:18.099 --> 26:20.924
Hey. Hockney said forget
about the computer right now

26:20.949 --> 26:22.516
and get over to the Roseland.

26:22.563 --> 26:24.484
She needs good eyes helping
with the security detail,

26:24.509 --> 26:25.664
and you've seen Brady in the flesh.

26:25.689 --> 26:27.039
They're not gonna evacuate?

26:27.221 --> 26:28.555
Yeah, based on what?

26:29.890 --> 26:31.341
How about the gala?

26:32.629 --> 26:34.147
H.Q.'s betting on Roseland.

26:35.703 --> 26:38.542
Yeah, all right. Uh, I'm heading over.

26:38.580 --> 26:40.133
Just let them know
I'm coming, will you?

26:40.174 --> 26:41.453
Yeah, talk soon.

27:01.028 --> 27:02.562
What is peace?

27:02.842 --> 27:05.970
Is what you call peace
the same peace as it is to me?

27:06.434 --> 27:08.522
Nah. Peace to me feels like I'm chained

27:08.603 --> 27:10.156
on a leash by the Devil himself,

27:10.207 --> 27:11.615
who's standing there laughing at me

27:11.640 --> 27:13.807
because, you see, as
long as I don't know me,

27:14.015 --> 27:16.250
he's winning, and I'll never be free.

27:21.577 --> 27:23.817
Wherefore art thou, Romeo?

27:24.016 --> 27:26.653
Deny thy father and refuse thy name,

27:26.928 --> 27:30.036
or, if thou wilt not,
be but sworn my love,

27:30.099 --> 27:31.994
and I'll no longer be a Capulet.

27:32.133 --> 27:33.880
Don't judge me, don't cast me out!

27:33.955 --> 27:36.390
Hear me out! Show... me out.

27:36.892 --> 27:38.365
Show me out of this void.

28:09.910 --> 28:11.044
Bullshit.

28:13.234 --> 28:15.135
Not going after any career night.

28:22.236 --> 28:24.238
Here! Over here.

29:33.774 --> 29:36.310
All right. Ticket?

29:39.669 --> 29:40.735
Thank you.

29:40.774 --> 29:41.976
You're welcome.

29:43.366 --> 29:45.265
Just lift the blanket.
Let me get a quick look here.

29:45.290 --> 29:47.057
Oh, of course, of course.

29:52.627 --> 29:53.761
Thank you.

29:53.835 --> 29:55.625
You're welcome.

29:56.213 --> 29:57.606
Next.

30:28.202 --> 30:30.403
Oh, I'm so glad we got to see this one.

30:38.779 --> 30:40.876
I said get out!

30:41.268 --> 30:44.293
Well, am I in danger right now?

30:44.395 --> 30:46.329
Just go to your son's house!

30:46.460 --> 30:49.505
Oh. He's kind of a bore.

30:49.550 --> 30:51.302
For God's sake, Ida, be bored!

30:51.328 --> 30:52.829
It's better than the alternative!

30:53.094 --> 30:54.628
Oh. Is it, really?

30:56.440 --> 30:57.657
For Christ's sake...

30:57.685 --> 30:59.098
And how am I supposed to go anywhere?

30:59.123 --> 31:01.524
- You're in my car.
- Well, call a cab.

31:01.589 --> 31:03.623
You're a great woman for giving advice.

31:03.777 --> 31:05.378
Just take it, for once!

31:18.518 --> 31:19.929
You guys got issued a picture.

31:19.954 --> 31:21.822
There he is. I think he's here.

31:22.490 --> 31:24.218
He's pretty dangerous.
Keep your eye out, all right?

31:24.243 --> 31:26.142
Got it.

31:27.120 --> 31:28.228
Arms out.

31:30.750 --> 31:32.569
Okay. Enjoy the show.

32:13.327 --> 32:14.461
Good evening.

32:14.569 --> 32:15.654
Good evening.

32:15.680 --> 32:17.234
Well, if you're here tonight,

32:17.259 --> 32:20.204
you're part of a very
special group... donors.

32:24.671 --> 32:26.472
We like money!

32:29.563 --> 32:31.736
But, seriously, you are
part of a special group.

32:31.780 --> 32:35.562
You're donors to this...
the Edmund Mills Art Center.

32:41.680 --> 32:44.692
This is a testament to...
to your excitement

32:44.717 --> 32:46.651
about arts in our community,

32:46.708 --> 32:48.152
arts in our school

32:48.445 --> 32:50.438
at a time when
it's not really important

32:50.471 --> 32:51.737
to a lot of people.

32:51.817 --> 32:53.957
But it is to us, and I thank...

32:54.015 --> 32:56.082
I really thank each
and every one of you.

32:56.263 --> 32:58.171
It's a very important
thing that you've done.

32:58.196 --> 32:59.597
I celebrate you.

33:04.869 --> 33:06.802
So good to see you here.

33:25.811 --> 33:27.237
Wait. Hold on.

33:31.397 --> 33:32.671
Thank you.

34:06.945 --> 34:08.087
Are you okay?

34:08.112 --> 34:09.208
Yeah, yeah, I'm grand.

34:09.234 --> 34:10.599
Well, you... you look terrible.

34:10.623 --> 34:11.875
I've been trying to call you.

34:11.900 --> 34:13.315
Well, I... I shut my phone off.

34:13.340 --> 34:14.350
Why?

34:14.400 --> 34:16.300
Because I do not want to speak
with my mother.

34:16.369 --> 34:17.902
So don't answer her calls.

34:18.137 --> 34:19.619
But that's rude.

34:19.665 --> 34:20.965
You got to get out of here.

34:21.333 --> 34:22.509
Wait. Why?

34:22.542 --> 34:23.775
I think he's here.

34:23.801 --> 34:24.773
Wait. He's alive?

34:24.797 --> 34:27.326
I think he could be anywhere
people I care about are.

34:27.875 --> 34:28.898
But...

34:28.922 --> 34:31.525
So you're implying
I'm someone you care about?

34:31.550 --> 34:34.481
In a paternalistic sense, yes.
You've got to go, please.

34:34.505 --> 34:35.871
Well, but if the feeling were mutual,

34:35.897 --> 34:36.978
then why would I leave you?

34:37.003 --> 34:38.771
For God's sake, will you go?!

34:39.324 --> 34:41.388
Well, Jerome is about
to speak in there.

34:41.487 --> 34:43.998
Get him and his family out of here now!

34:44.024 --> 34:46.592
O-Okay.

35:02.335 --> 35:05.918
[Cheers and applause

35:05.943 --> 35:09.416
I'm here tonight to introduce
a very, very special young man.

35:10.376 --> 35:12.732
And, by the way, if there's
a 17-year-old in town

35:12.757 --> 35:15.191
 that could run against me and win...

35:15.454 --> 35:17.651
it's this guy.

35:17.697 --> 35:19.930
So I'm glad that you're
going off to college, son.

35:21.280 --> 35:23.838
He's the first in a generation
to get into Harvard.

35:26.315 --> 35:27.461
Yeah!

35:27.486 --> 35:28.753
The first in five years

35:28.778 --> 35:30.783
to be admitted into
the National Honor Society.

35:40.152 --> 35:41.487
Excuse me.

35:46.646 --> 35:48.314
Excuse me.

35:59.251 --> 36:00.786
Brady?

36:02.922 --> 36:04.656
Should've worn sunglasses.

36:04.991 --> 36:06.558
Wait, wait!

36:06.766 --> 36:08.887
Aah! Aah!

36:09.014 --> 36:10.554
Aah!

36:37.943 --> 36:39.490
Mr. Jerome Robinson.

36:48.313 --> 36:49.953
Thank you, Mayor.

36:50.162 --> 36:51.762
And... And thank you all

36:51.787 --> 36:53.946
for supporting
the Edmund Mills Art Center.

36:53.971 --> 36:55.838
This is becoming the cornerstone

36:55.863 --> 36:57.998
of the revitalization of downtown.

36:58.143 --> 36:59.445
So thank you for being here,

36:59.470 --> 37:02.904
and thank you for donating
and joining us here.

37:11.544 --> 37:13.810
Tonight you've seen incredible
artists, musicians,

37:13.835 --> 37:16.636
dancers, poets, painters...
you name it.

37:17.109 --> 37:18.977
Tonight, we're gonna watch

37:19.031 --> 37:21.136
the Bridgton Middle School Choir
perform.

37:21.200 --> 37:22.315
So, ladies and gentlemen,

37:22.340 --> 37:24.822
please give it up for the
Bridgton Middle School Choir.

37:24.921 --> 37:26.021
Yes.

37:30.617 --> 37:32.285
Whoo!

37:43.390 --> 37:44.990
Help me.

37:45.811 --> 37:47.279
Help me!

37:48.727 --> 37:50.601
Help me! Help me!

37:50.756 --> 37:53.825
Help me! Help me! Somebody help me!

37:57.349 --> 37:58.479
Help me!

38:07.073 --> 38:08.106
Help me.

38:08.154 --> 38:09.788
Call a medic, quickly!

38:10.025 --> 38:11.245
Help!

38:11.270 --> 38:12.285
All right.

38:20.630 --> 38:21.823
It's Brady.

38:21.848 --> 38:23.315
Here. H-Hold this to the wound.

38:24.287 --> 38:25.714
It's... It's Brady.

38:25.872 --> 38:27.673
It's Brady Hartsfield.

38:27.853 --> 38:29.320
Please...

38:29.361 --> 38:30.448
Where? Where is he?

38:30.473 --> 38:31.740
He's in a wheelchair.

38:31.765 --> 38:33.966
Please don't leave me here.

38:33.991 --> 38:35.501
I don't want to die here!

38:35.526 --> 38:37.104
You're not gonna die, all right?

38:37.129 --> 38:39.130
Just hold this to stem the bleeding.

38:39.155 --> 38:40.555
It's all gonna be fine.

38:40.860 --> 38:42.060
You see which way he went?

38:42.121 --> 38:43.455
Sir, I got this.

38:44.142 --> 38:46.601
Wait. He's got... He shaved his head.

38:47.043 --> 38:48.143
Ow.

38:48.168 --> 38:49.401
He shaved his head.

38:49.712 --> 38:50.922
He wh... He what?

38:51.531 --> 38:53.040
Shaved his... Shaved his head?

38:53.065 --> 38:54.932
Got a shaved head.

38:55.107 --> 38:57.547
Just don't let him come back here.

38:57.669 --> 39:00.805
Please don't let him come back here!

40:20.858 --> 40:22.584
- Jerome, I just saw Hodges.
- Yeah.

40:22.609 --> 40:24.067
I just saw Hodges.
He said that Brady's here.

40:24.092 --> 40:25.164
You got to get everyone out of here.

40:25.189 --> 40:26.247
Wait, wait. Slow down. What now?

40:26.272 --> 40:27.580
I just saw Hodges.
Get everyone out of here!

40:27.605 --> 40:28.960
- Go, go, go, go!
- You said Brady's here?

40:28.985 --> 40:30.016
Yes, go.

40:31.761 --> 40:33.543
Hey, guys, go this way. Everybody, out!

40:33.579 --> 40:34.756
Get back.

40:35.927 --> 40:37.386
Everybody, down!

40:39.224 --> 40:40.252
Everybody, down!

40:40.320 --> 40:43.154
Freeze!

40:43.213 --> 40:44.300
Get down, get down! Get down!

40:44.325 --> 40:45.325
Freeze!

41:07.606 --> 41:09.073
Mike Sturdivant?

41:59.424 --> 42:01.892
...responsible for the
capture and arrest

42:01.917 --> 42:03.790
of the infamous Mercedes killer

42:03.863 --> 42:05.447
when they stepped in to stop him

42:05.472 --> 42:07.427
from committing another atrocious act.

42:13.759 --> 42:16.165
How long is the drive?

42:17.015 --> 42:18.215
It's about 10 hours.

42:18.504 --> 42:19.703
Oof.

42:19.728 --> 42:21.596
Yeah.

42:25.418 --> 42:27.155
So...

42:28.260 --> 42:31.004
What you got going on today?

42:31.563 --> 42:34.219
Well... I...

42:34.440 --> 42:36.612
They're coming in for me
in a few minutes.

42:37.930 --> 42:39.965
Get me on my feet...

42:39.991 --> 42:42.091
just a little walk
up and down the corridor,

42:42.116 --> 42:43.565
so that's really good.

42:44.198 --> 42:45.218
Yeah.

42:45.243 --> 42:46.659
- Yeah?
- That is good.

42:48.908 --> 42:50.376
Yep.

42:53.459 --> 42:55.261
Yep.

43:00.238 --> 43:02.306
It's a long drive.

43:05.651 --> 43:08.453
Yeah, it's a long drive.

43:10.435 --> 43:11.736
Yeah.

43:14.307 --> 43:16.603
Your future awaits.

43:34.997 --> 43:36.665
Thanks, Bill.

43:37.136 --> 43:39.132
Drive safe.

43:39.711 --> 43:41.245
Yeah, I'll try.

46:27.846 --> 46:29.913
This is it, Kermit William.

46:30.188 --> 46:32.142
You're busting out of here in the A.M.

46:32.170 --> 46:33.571
You shit me not?

46:34.053 --> 46:35.835
I shit you not.

46:37.459 --> 46:40.264
I'll take care of this,
and I'll be back for those.

46:40.862 --> 46:42.125
Thanks, Al.

47:33.238 --> 47:35.106
Can I pop in here a second?

47:37.062 --> 47:38.229
Is the doctor in?

47:38.254 --> 47:39.723
In with him now.

47:39.910 --> 47:41.531
Okay. Thanks.

47:41.673 --> 47:43.141
Thanks.

47:51.436 --> 47:53.396
Hey.

47:54.733 --> 47:56.467
You're leaving today, I hear.

47:56.628 --> 47:59.382
That mean you're gonna stop
coming in here to stare at him?

48:01.493 --> 48:03.262
Unlikely.

48:04.656 --> 48:08.225
The path leading up to the front
of this hospital is brick.

48:08.687 --> 48:11.748
Hunch down and stare at those
bricks on your way out.

48:11.849 --> 48:14.181
They'll communicate better
than he will, Mr. Hodges.

48:14.259 --> 48:15.581
He's gone.

48:19.505 --> 48:20.805
Never coming back?

48:20.959 --> 48:22.840
No.

48:23.029 --> 48:25.497
His brain has the same
electromagnetic level

48:25.522 --> 48:28.759
as a triple-A battery you left
in a remote five years ago.

48:33.552 --> 48:36.454
If I whack that remote enough,

48:36.515 --> 48:39.383
I'll get the TV running, I promise you.

48:39.410 --> 48:41.849
If somebody whacks him
one more time, he'll die.

48:45.530 --> 48:47.554
Care to take a coffee break, Doc?

48:47.719 --> 48:49.521
Be like I was never here.

48:51.270 --> 48:53.804
If he ever flatlines,
I hope you have an alibi.

48:53.912 --> 48:57.616
If he ever flatlines, I'll show
up and cremate him myself.

48:59.571 --> 49:01.138
You think I'm joking.

49:02.113 --> 49:05.050
Sadly, I don't.

49:08.231 --> 49:10.128
I'll just be a second here.

49:30.281 --> 49:33.244
I know you're in there...

49:33.698 --> 49:36.538
because hate hangs on...

49:36.792 --> 49:39.211
and hate's all you had.

49:42.092 --> 49:43.949
Could bring you back someday.

49:48.133 --> 49:51.169
Sure as taxes and Christmas, though,

49:51.350 --> 49:54.219
I'll be waiting...

49:54.632 --> 49:57.234
and I'll finish it.

